320
00:12:29,670 --> 00:12:30,910
Jens to the recipient list.

321
00:12:31,490 --> 00:12:32,590
There's two problems with that.

322
00:12:32,710 --> 00:12:35,930
For starters, because we branched the conversation up

323
00:12:35,930 --> 00:12:38,290
here, that last email message would not contain

324
00:12:38,290 --> 00:12:41,730
the entire conversation, but also, if Stephanie then

325
00:12:41,730 --> 00:12:44,310
later, when it replied to an earlier message

326
00:12:44,310 --> 00:12:46,170
of mine, Jens wouldn't get that anyway.

327
00:12:46,330 --> 00:12:47,550
You end up with these cat-and-mouse

328
00:12:47,550 --> 00:12:47,970
games.

329
00:12:48,590 --> 00:12:50,530
In the Wave model, all you have to

330
00:12:50,530 --> 00:12:53,310
